======================================================================
PART 6: THE 3/2 RATIO — JACOBSTHAL PERSPECTIVE
======================================================================

  J_2(n) = (2^n - (-1)^n) / 3
  J_6(n) = (3^n - (-2)^n) / 5

  Ratio J_6(n)/J_2(n) → (3/2)^n · 3/5 as n → ∞

  At the OCF level:
    H = I(CG, 2) = 1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂ + 8α₃
    I₃ = I(CG, 3) = 1 + 3α₁ + 9α₂ + 27α₃
    I₆ = I(CG, 6) = 1 + 6α₁ + 36α₂ + 216α₃

  Ratio I₃/H within lambda fibers ≈ 3/2 (proved!)

  What about I₆/H ratio?

  I₆/H ratio: mean=3.5179, std=0.4951
  I₃/H ratio: mean=1.3167, std=0.1265

